Package ohos.event.intentagent

Class IntentAgentInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.intentagent.IntentAgentInfo

  • public final class IntentAgentInfo
extends Object
    A parametric class that contains the parameters required by IntentAgentHelper#getIntentAgent.

    This class is used to encapsulate parameters requestCode, operationType, flag, intents, and extraInfo. It is used as the input parameter for the IntentAgentHelper#getIntentAgent method.

    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Notification#ANS

        public IntentAgentInfo​(int requestCode,
                       IntentAgentConstant.OperationType operationType,
                       IntentAgentConstant.Flags flag,
                       List<Intent> intents,
                       IntentParams extraInfo)
        A constructor used to create an IntentAgentInfo instance based on the input parameters.
        Parameters:
        requestCode - Indicates the request code to set. It is a private value defined by the user.
        operationType - Indicates the type of the operation to be performed by the IntentAgent object. For details about the value range, see IntentAgentConstant.OperationType.
        flag - Indicates the flag for handling the IntentAgent. For details about the value range, see IntentAgentConstant.Flags.
        intents - Indicates the collection of Intent objects to be used for creating the IntentAgent object. The number of intents in the collection is determined by IntentAgentConstant.OperationType.
        extraInfo - Indicates the extra information to be used for creating the IntentAgent object.
